With this kind of documentation customers can understand the impact of the use of this field and why JIRA behaves in this way.

*Summary*
When default language is not set to English, REST API to [update|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/latest/#d2e2937] remaining estimate will fail with the following error. It will require original estimate to be edited as well. 
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [],
    "errors": {
        "timetracking_originalestimate": "L'estimation originale spécifiée n'est pas valide."
    }
}
{code}

*Steps to reproduce*
# Change default language to French in General Configuration
# Disable time tracking 
# Modify the time format from {{pretty}} to {{days}}
# Enable time tracking
# Create an issue with {{originalestimate}} and {{remainingestimate}} = 3d
# Edit issue via REST
# Modify remaining estimate to 2d

*Affected behavior*
Language set to Deutsch, French are affected

