At the moment, Time Tracking doesn't account for indexing in languages other than English.

*Steps to reproduce*
# Change Default language in General Configuration to *français (France)* or Language Preference in Profile to *français (France)*
# Change indexing language to french.
# Disable Time Tracking.
# Set time format to *jours*
!jours.png|thumbnail!
# View an issue. Time Tracking should be shown like this:
!french.png|thumbnail!
# Edit the issue
# Use 'j' instead of 'd'. This error will be prompted:
!edit-error.png|thumbnail!

*Affected processes*
* Issue cannot be edited if the value is entered as 'j'
* REST API will fail with this error:
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [],
    "errors": {
        "timetracking_originalestimate": "L'estimation originale spécifiée n'est pas valide."
    }
}
{code}

*Expected behavior*
{{original estimate}} or {{remaining estimate}} should read 'j' as 'd'

{panel:title=Workaround|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Use 'd' for {{original estimate}} or {{remaining estimate}} when editing issue. 
{panel}

